      <abstract>
        <p>The title compound, 3,5-bis(2-hydroxybenzylidene)piperidin-4-one (<bold>3</bold>), was prepared via reaction of 2-hydroxybenzaldehyde (<bold>1</bold>) and 4-piperidone (<bold>2</bold>) under microwave irradiation in the presence of 10% NaOH solution. The compound was fully characterized from its UV, IR, NMR and MS data.</p>
      </abstract>
